name: ship-it-checklist
description: Pre-release verification checklist for mobile apps - never forget rollback plans, monitoring, or app store requirements

# Purpose
Systematically verify everything before shipping. Prevent "oh no, I forgot X" moments. Ship with confidence.

# When to use
Use this skill when:
- Preparing a release (any environment)
- Deploying new features
- Making database migrations
- Updating third-party dependencies
- Before app store submissions
- After hotfixes

# Inputs
- What's being shipped (features, fixes, changes)
- Target environment (staging, production)
- Release type (major, minor, patch, hotfix)
- Timeline constraints

# Output Format (required)
1) Release summary (what's shipping)
2) Pre-flight checklist (by category)
3) Rollback plan
4) Monitoring plan
5) Communication plan
6) Post-release verification

# Pre-Flight Checklist

## Code Quality
- [ ] All tests passing (unit, integration, e2e)
- [ ] No new warnings/lints introduced
- [ ] Code reviewed and approved
- [ ] No debug code left in (print statements, TODO hacks)
- [ ] No hardcoded test credentials or URLs
- [ ] Feature flags configured correctly

## Database/Backend (Supabase)
- [ ] Migrations tested on staging
- [ ] Migrations are backwards-compatible (or coordinated)
- [ ] RLS policies reviewed for new tables
- [ ] Indexes added for new query patterns
- [ ] Edge functions deployed and tested
- [ ] Realtime subscriptions verified
- [ ] No breaking API changes (or versioned)

## Mobile App Specific
- [ ] Tested on both iOS and Android
- [ ] Tested on minimum supported OS versions
- [ ] Tested on low-end device (or emulator)
- [ ] Offline behavior verified
- [ ] Deep links working
- [ ] Push notifications working
- [ ] Permissions requested appropriately

## Performance
- [ ] No obvious performance regressions
- [ ] Startup time acceptable
- [ ] Memory usage stable
- [ ] No new ANRs or jank

## Security
- [ ] No secrets in code or logs
- [ ] Auth flows tested
- [ ] Sensitive data handling reviewed
- [ ] New endpoints have proper authorization

# Environment-Specific Checklists

## Staging Release
- [ ] Staging environment matches production config
- [ ] Test accounts available
- [ ] Staging data is realistic
- [ ] QA sign-off (if applicable)

## Production Release
- [ ] Staging release verified
- [ ] Version number incremented
- [ ] Changelog updated
- [ ] Release notes prepared
- [ ] Support team informed
- [ ] Rollback plan documented
- [ ] Monitoring dashboards ready

## App Store Release (iOS/Android)
- [ ] Version/build numbers correct
- [ ] App store metadata updated
- [ ] Screenshots current
- [ ] Privacy policy updated (if needed)
- [ ] New permissions explained
- [ ] Compliance requirements met (GDPR, etc.)
- [ ] Phased rollout configured (recommended)
- [ ] Previous version still available (staged rollout)

# Rollback Plan Template

```markdown
## Rollback Plan for v{X.Y.Z}

### Triggers for Rollback
- Crash rate > {X}%
- Error rate > {X}%
- Critical user flow broken
- Security vulnerability discovered

### Mobile App Rollback
1. Halt staged rollout in App Store Connect / Play Console
2. If critical: Request expedited review for hotfix
3. Communicate with affected users
4. Document incident

### Backend Rollback (Supabase)
1. Revert edge function: `supabase functions deploy {name} --version {prev}`
2. Revert migration (if safe): Run down migration
3. If data corrupted: Restore from backup
4. Update app to handle both states

### Database Migration Rollback
- Migration reversible: Yes/No
- If No: Forward-fix plan: {describe}
- Backup timestamp: {time}
- Restore procedure: {link or steps}

### Point of No Return
- After {X hours/days} with no issues, rollback becomes complex
- Data migrations may not be reversible after {condition}
```

# Monitoring Plan

## What to Watch (First 24 Hours)

### Crash Monitoring
- Firebase Crashlytics / Sentry
- Alert threshold: > {X} crashes per hour
- Compare to previous version baseline

### Error Rates
- API error rates (Supabase dashboard)
- Client-side errors (logging service)
- Alert threshold: > {X}% error rate

### Performance
- App startup time
- API response times (p50, p95, p99)
- Frame rate / jank metrics

### Business Metrics
- User signups/logins
- Core action completion rate
- Revenue (if applicable)

## Monitoring Checklist
- [ ] Dashboards created/updated
- [ ] Alerts configured
- [ ] On-call person identified
- [ ] Escalation path clear

# Communication Plan

## Internal Communication
- [ ] Team notified of release time
- [ ] Release notes shared internally
- [ ] Known issues documented
- [ ] Support team briefed

## External Communication (if needed)
- [ ] Changelog published
- [ ] Social media post (if major release)
- [ ] Email to users (if major changes)
- [ ] In-app announcement (if needed)

# Post-Release Verification

## Immediate (0-1 hour)
- [ ] App downloadable from store
- [ ] Core flows working (login, main features)
- [ ] No spike in crashes
- [ ] Backend healthy

## Short-term (1-24 hours)
- [ ] Error rates stable
- [ ] Performance metrics normal
- [ ] User feedback reviewed
- [ ] No critical issues reported

## Medium-term (1-7 days)
- [ ] Staged rollout progressing
- [ ] Metrics trending positively
- [ ] No delayed-onset issues
- [ ] Full rollout decision made

# Release Types Quick Reference

## Hotfix (Critical Bug)
| Step | Time |
|------|------|
| Identify and fix | ASAP |
| Minimal testing | 1-2 hours |
| Deploy to production | Immediate |
| Monitor closely | 24 hours |

## Patch (Bug Fixes)
| Step | Time |
|------|------|
| Accumulate fixes | 1-2 weeks |
| Full test cycle | 1-2 days |
| Staged rollout | 3-7 days |
| Full rollout | After verification |

## Minor (New Features)
| Step | Time |
|------|------|
| Feature complete | Sprint end |
| QA and testing | 1 week |
| Staged rollout (10%) | 2-3 days |
| Increase rollout | Gradual |
| Full rollout | After 1-2 weeks |

## Major (Breaking Changes)
| Step | Time |
|------|------|
| Migration planning | 2-4 weeks before |
| Beta testing | 1-2 weeks |
| Staged rollout (1%) | 1 week |
| Gradual increase | 2-4 weeks |
| Full rollout | After thorough verification |

# Feature Flags Checklist

## Before Release
- [ ] Flag created and named clearly
- [ ] Default value is safe (usually off)
- [ ] Flag documented
- [ ] Kill switch tested

## During Rollout
- [ ] Enable for internal users first
- [ ] Enable for beta users
- [ ] Gradual percentage rollout
- [ ] Monitor metrics at each stage

## After Successful Rollout
- [ ] Flag set to 100%
- [ ] Flag removal scheduled
- [ ] Code cleanup ticket created

# Common Mistakes to Avoid

- Skipping staging (even for "small" changes)
- No rollback plan for database migrations
- Releasing on Friday afternoon
- Not monitoring after release
- Forgetting to update version numbers
- Leaving feature flags on forever
- Not testing on real devices
- Ignoring app store review guidelines
- Releasing without changelog
- No communication to support team

# Emergency Release Protocol

1. **Assess severity** (P0-P3)
2. **Notify stakeholders** immediately for P0/P1
3. **Fix in isolation** (branch from production)
4. **Minimal testing** (affected flow only)
5. **Deploy with monitoring**
6. **Post-incident review** within 48 hours
7. **Document lessons learned**

# Release Confidence Levels

| Level | Criteria | Action |
|-------|----------|--------|
| High | All checks pass, tested thoroughly | Full rollout |
| Medium | Minor concerns, no blockers | Staged rollout, close monitoring |
| Low | Known issues, time pressure | Small percentage, ready to halt |
| None | Critical issues found | Do not release |
